UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1760
1 A RESOLUTION reaffirming the authority of locally elected school boards to
2 govern school districts through policy and procedure in accordance with state law.
3 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth of Kentucky has long recognized that locally
4 elected boards of education are best positioned to govern school districts in a manner
5 responsive to their communities; and
6 WHEREAS, the Kentucky Revised Statutes clearly vest governing authority,
7 policy-making power, and oversight responsibility in local boards of education; and
8 WHEREAS, KRS 160.160 establishes that members of local boards of education
9 are elected by the voters of their districts and are directly accountable to the public they
10 serve; and
11 WHEREAS, KRS 160.290 assigns to local boards of education the general control
12 and management of the public schools within their district, including the adoption of
13 policies, rules, and procedures necessary for effective operations; and
14 WHEREAS, KRS 160.340 authorizes local boards of education to adopt and
15 enforce policies governing personnel, students, operations, and administration consistent
16 with state law; and
17 WHEREAS, KRS 158.645 and 158.6453 recognize that while statewide standards
18 exist, local boards retain discretion in implementation through locally adopted policies
19 and procedures; and
20 WHEREAS, recent actions, directives, and practices, whether intentional or
21 inadvertent, have risked blurring or diminishing the lawful authority of locally elected
22 school boards by bypassing, undermining, and disregarding duly adopted board policies;
23 and
24 WHEREAS, preservation of local control through elected governance is essential to
25 transparency, accountability, parental trust, and constitutional principles of a
26 representative government;
27 NOW, THEREFORE,
Page 1 of 2
