UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1760
1 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
2 Kentucky:
3 Section 1. The Senate hereby reaffirms the authority of locally elected boards of
4 education as the controlling governance structure under state law to govern school
5 districts through duly adopted policies and procedures.
6 Section 2. The Senate reaffirms that:
7 (1) An individual administrator, employee, external agency, or non-elected body
8 shall not supersede, disregard, or act contrary to local school board-adopted policy unless
9 expressly authorized by Acts of the General Assembly, federal law, or lawful local board
10 of education action;
11 (2) All district operations, administrative decisions, and enforcement actions shall
12 be conducted in strict accordance with policies adopted by the local board of education,
13 consistent with the Kentucky Revised Statutes;
14 (3) The roles of superintendents and administrators are to carry out and
15 administer local board of education policy, and not to create de facto policy through
16 unilateral action; and
17 (4) Any practice that circumvents local board of education authority or excludes
18 the board from its statutory role in governance is inconsistent with Kentucky law and
19 public accountability.
20 Section 3. This Resolution shall serve as the Senate's formal affirmation of local
21 school board authority.
22 Section 4. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
23 Resolution to Senator Aaron Reed, and copies to the Kentucky Department of Education,
24 300 Sower Blvd. 5th Floor, Frankfort, Kentucky 40601, for distribution to each school
25 district.
